00:22:08,727 --> 00:22:13,926
Awaken to triumph again
in the face of yet another day,

274
00:22:13,999 --> 00:22:17,560
another step
in our unified march

275
00:22:17,636 --> 00:22:21,231
- into the unwavering purpose...
- [ Thunder rumbles ]

276
00:22:21,306 --> 00:22:25,208
[ Voice fades ]

277
00:22:25,277 --> 00:22:27,939
...move ahead together

278
00:22:28,013 --> 00:22:31,608
into the certainty
of our collective destiny.

279
00:22:43,028 --> 00:22:44,552
[ Faucet squeaks ]

280
00:22:49,868 --> 00:22:52,098
[ Glass shatters ]

281
00:22:52,170 --> 00:22:54,001
ROBBIE:
What are you doing?

282
00:22:57,375 --> 00:22:59,605
I said, what are you doing?

283
00:22:59,678 --> 00:23:03,136
I accidently dropped my...

284
00:23:03,215 --> 00:23:04,773
morning interval.

285
00:23:04,849 --> 00:23:07,841
I took it out
before I brushed my teeth.

286
00:23:09,020 --> 00:23:11,420
I never take it out
before I brush my teeth.

287
00:23:11,489 --> 00:23:15,391
Then you'll go by Equilibrium,
log the loss,

288
00:23:15,460 --> 00:23:16,791
and get a replacement.

289
00:23:18,363 --> 00:23:19,796
Yes.

290
00:23:19,864 --> 00:23:21,627
Of course.

291
00:23:42,320 --> 00:23:44,584
Your new partner called.

292
00:23:44,656 --> 00:23:47,022
He says he'll pick you up
at 10:00 for the A.N.R.

293
00:23:47,092 --> 00:23:48,423
I hope you don't mind.

294
00:23:48,493 --> 00:23:50,825
I took the liberty
of telling him

295
00:23:50,895 --> 00:23:53,989
you would be at Equilibrium,
replacing your dose.

296
00:23:55,066 --> 00:23:56,590
No, of course not.

297
00:23:56,668 --> 00:23:58,602
That was the right thing
to do.

298
00:23:58,670 --> 00:24:01,537
[ Rattling ]

299
00:24:01,606 --> 00:24:03,972
Stop that.

300
00:24:11,082 --> 00:24:13,846
MAN AND WOMAN ALTERNATING:
Due to terrorist activity,

301
00:24:13,918 --> 00:24:16,352
this site is
temporarily closed.

302
00:24:16,421 --> 00:24:21,859
Proceed to the Equilibrium
Center in Sector 8A.

303
00:24:23,094 --> 00:24:25,324
Due to terrorist activity,

304
00:24:25,397 --> 00:24:27,695
this site is
temporarily closed.

305
00:24:27,766 --> 00:24:30,200
MAN: This site is
temporarily closed.

306
00:24:30,268 --> 00:24:34,728
Proceed to the Equilibrium
Center in Sector 8A.

307
00:24:39,744 --> 00:24:41,507
More than punctual, Cleric.

308
00:24:41,579 --> 00:24:42,739
Hop in.

309
00:24:54,459 --> 00:24:55,721
[ Tires screech ]

310
00:24:55,794 --> 00:24:57,489
How were the lines?

311
00:24:57,562 --> 00:24:59,996
I'm surprised you were able
to get your interval

312
00:25:00,065 --> 00:25:01,726
and get out so quickly.

313
00:25:03,001 --> 00:25:05,026
No, they're...
they're fine today.

314
00:25:06,404 --> 00:25:08,929
[ Engine idling ]

315
00:25:09,007 --> 00:25:12,238
Maybe I'll drop by later,
get my interval adjusted.

316
00:25:12,310 --> 00:25:13,743
[ Gun cocks ]

317
00:25:13,812 --> 00:25:16,007
You expecting Resistance?

318
00:25:16,081 --> 00:25:19,278
That's something you'll find
about me, Cleric.

319
00:25:19,351 --> 00:25:23,378
I'm a wary person,
cautious by nature.

320
00:25:24,723 --> 00:25:27,055
Always expecting the worst.

321
00:25:27,125 --> 00:25:29,422
[ Thud, metal rattles ]

322
00:25:29,494 --> 00:25:30,791
You can't do this.
You cannot do this.

323
00:25:30,862 --> 00:25:33,922
Tetragrammaton.
There's nothing we can't do.

324
00:25:33,998 --> 00:25:35,124
[ Grunts ]

325
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:37,134
How long have you been off
the dose?

326
00:25:37,202 --> 00:25:38,294
Look at you.

327
00:25:38,369 --> 00:25:39,427
[ Gasps ]

328
00:25:39,504 --> 00:25:41,096
Look at you!

329
00:25:41,172 --> 00:25:42,867
[ Breathing heavily ]

330
00:25:48,112 --> 00:25:49,272
Look at you.

331
00:25:51,482 --> 00:25:54,042
The mirror's frame is illegal.
Destroy it.

332
00:26:02,927 --> 00:26:05,760
MAN: We have suppression.
We're making entry.

333
00:26:05,830 --> 00:26:07,263
MAN #2: Standard deployment.

334
00:26:07,332 --> 00:26:10,130
Collecting catalog.
Illegal articles.

335
00:26:10,201 --> 00:26:11,964
[ Glass shatters ]

336
00:26:56,180 --> 00:26:57,977
You're gonna burn it,
aren't you?

337
00:26:58,049 --> 00:26:59,141
[ Bell jingles ]

338
00:26:59,217 --> 00:27:00,684
Eventually.

339
00:27:00,752 --> 00:27:03,448
However, you couldn't have
accumulated all this

340
00:27:03,521 --> 00:27:04,783
by yourself.

341
00:27:04,856 --> 00:27:07,848
It'll all be sorted
and examined.

342
00:27:07,925 --> 00:27:11,053
We'll discover
who your confederates are.

343
00:27:12,697 --> 00:27:13,721
Gun!

344
00:27:25,877 --> 00:27:28,072
[ Breathing heavily ]

345
00:27:31,482 --> 00:27:33,143
We need her.

346
00:27:59,344 --> 00:28:00,333
What's your name?

347
00:28:00,411 --> 00:28:03,608
O'Brien, Mary.

348
00:28:03,681 --> 00:28:06,912
Well, Mary...

349
00:28:06,984 --> 00:28:08,383
you can either wait

350
00:28:08,453 --> 00:28:12,549
and tell the technicians
at the Palace of Justice...

351
00:28:12,623 --> 00:28:15,387
or you can tell me now.

352
00:28:15,460 --> 00:28:17,451
Who are your friends?

353
00:28:21,165 --> 00:28:23,690
I'm wondering if you have
any idea at all

354
00:28:23,768 --> 00:28:26,794
what that word means--
"friend."

355
00:28:30,174 --> 00:28:32,335
There's nothing
you don't feel?

356
00:28:34,011 --> 00:28:35,535
How about guilt?

357
00:28:37,382 --> 00:28:39,577
Let me ask you something.

358
00:28:47,191 --> 00:28:48,283
[ Glass clatters ]

359
00:28:48,359 --> 00:28:51,089
Why are you alive?

360
00:28:54,332 --> 00:28:56,823
I'm alive...

361
00:29:01,172 --> 00:29:02,503
I live...

362
00:29:05,009 --> 00:29:08,467
...to safeguard the continuity
of this great society.

363
00:29:08,546 --> 00:29:10,138
To serve Libria.

364
00:29:10,214 --> 00:29:11,647
It's circular.

365
00:29:11,716 --> 00:29:14,310
You exist to continue
your existence.

366
00:29:14,385 --> 00:29:15,875
What's the point?

367
00:29:18,055 --> 00:29:19,818
What's the point
of <i>your</i> existence?

368
00:29:19,891 --> 00:29:21,415
To feel.

369
00:29:21,492 --> 00:29:24,655
'Cause you've never done it,
you can never know it.

370
00:29:24,729 --> 00:29:27,493
But it's as vital as breath.

371
00:29:27,565 --> 00:29:30,193
And without it--
without love,

372
00:29:30,268 --> 00:29:33,760
without anger,
without sorrow--

373
00:29:33,838 --> 00:29:38,207
breath is
just a clock ticking.

374
00:29:42,447 --> 00:29:45,245
Then I have no choice
but to remand you

375
00:29:45,316 --> 00:29:47,546
to the Palace of Justice
for processing.

376
00:29:49,187 --> 00:29:50,950
Processing.

377
00:29:54,125 --> 00:29:56,286
You mean execution, don't you?

378
00:29:58,696 --> 00:30:00,357
Processing.

379
00:30:08,339 --> 00:30:10,239
The Gun Katas.

380
00:30:10,308 --> 00:30:13,243
Through analysis of thousands
of recorded gunfights,

381
00:30:13,311 --> 00:30:15,211
the Cleric has determined

382
00:30:15,280 --> 00:30:18,477
that the geometric distribution
of antagonists in any gun battle

383
00:30:18,550 --> 00:30:21,212
is a statistically
predictable element.

384
00:30:21,286 --> 00:30:24,722
MAN: The Gun Kata treats
the gun as a total weapon,

385
00:30:24,789 --> 00:30:27,053
each fluid position
representing

386
00:30:27,125 --> 00:30:30,151
a maximum kill zone,
inflicting maximum damage

387
00:30:30,228 --> 00:30:32,093
on the maximum number
of opponents

388
00:30:32,163 --> 00:30:33,892
while keeping
the defender clear

389
00:30:33,965 --> 00:30:36,229
of the statistically
traditional trajectories

390
00:30:36,301 --> 00:30:37,962
of return fire.

391
00:30:39,137 --> 00:30:41,071
DUPONT: By the rote mastery
of this art,

392
00:30:41,139 --> 00:30:44,370
your firing efficiency will rise
by no less than 120%.

393
00:30:44,442 --> 00:30:48,003
The difference of a 63% increase
to lethal proficiency

394
00:30:48,079 --> 00:30:50,445
makes the master
of the Gun Katas

395
00:30:50,515 --> 00:30:54,417
an adversary not to be
taken lightly.

396
00:31:43,668 --> 00:31:44,794
[ Thud ]

397
00:31:44,869 --> 00:31:47,599
O'BRIEN: [ Echoing ]
Without love...

398
00:31:47,672 --> 00:31:51,233
breath is just a clock...
ticking.

399
00:31:51,309 --> 00:31:53,777
[ Flames roaring ]

400
00:31:53,845 --> 00:31:55,437
[ Gasps ]

401
00:31:55,513 --> 00:31:59,279
[ Breathing heavily ]

402
00:31:59,350 --> 00:32:02,842
[ Heart beating ]

403
00:32:17,268 --> 00:32:20,465
[ Thunder rumbles ]

404
00:32:32,517 --> 00:32:35,077
[ Thunder rumbles ]

405
00:32:35,153 --> 00:32:37,519
[ Breathing heavily ]

406
00:32:56,708 --> 00:32:58,869
[ Thunder rumbles ]

407
00:33:24,402 --> 00:33:26,063
[ Whirs ]

408
00:33:32,510 --> 00:33:36,503
DUPONT: Prozium--
the great nepenthe.

409
00:33:36,581 --> 00:33:38,776
Opiate of our masses.

410
00:33:38,850 --> 00:33:41,444
Glue of our great society.

411
00:33:41,519 --> 00:33:43,612
Salve and salvation,

412
00:33:43,688 --> 00:33:47,624
it has delivered us
from pathos, from sorrow,

413
00:33:47,692 --> 00:33:51,753
the deepest chasms
of melancholy and hate.

414
00:33:51,829 --> 00:33:54,354
With it, we anesthetize grief,

415
00:33:54,432 --> 00:33:58,528
annihilate jealousy,
obliterate rage.

416
00:33:58,603 --> 00:34:03,040
That those sister impulses
towards joy, love, and elation

417
00:34:03,107 --> 00:34:05,667
are anesthetized in stride,

418
00:34:05,743 --> 00:34:08,041
we accept as fair sacrifice.

419
00:34:08,112 --> 00:34:14,073
For we embrace Prozium
in its unifying fullness

420
00:34:14,152 --> 00:34:18,384
and all that it has done
to make us great.

421
00:34:27,165 --> 00:34:29,156
[ Loud footsteps ]

422
00:35:11,409 --> 00:35:12,808
Good morning, Cleric.

423
00:35:12,877 --> 00:35:14,811
Good morning.

424
00:35:14,879 --> 00:35:18,940
...intrinsically, humans,
as creatures of the Earth

425
00:35:19,016 --> 00:35:25,251
were drawn inherently always
back to one thing-- war.

426
00:35:25,323 --> 00:35:28,622
And thus we seek to correct
not the symptom

427
00:35:28,693 --> 00:35:31,253
but the disease itself.

428
00:35:31,329 --> 00:35:34,787
We have sought to shrug off
individuality,

429
00:35:34,866 --> 00:35:37,494
replacing it with conformity.

430
00:35:37,568 --> 00:35:40,469
Replacing it...

431
00:35:40,538 --> 00:35:43,268
with sameness...

432
00:35:43,341 --> 00:35:45,832
with unity,

433
00:35:45,910 --> 00:35:50,472
allowing each man, woman,
and child

434
00:35:50,548 --> 00:35:52,379
in this great society

435
00:35:52,450 --> 00:35:56,011
to lead identical lives.

436
00:35:57,555 --> 00:36:01,047
The concept of identical
environment construction

437
00:36:01,125 --> 00:36:04,390
allows each of us to head
confidently into each moment

438
00:36:04,462 --> 00:36:06,191
with all the secure knowledge

439
00:36:06,264 --> 00:36:09,097
it has been lived before.

440
00:36:09,166 --> 00:36:11,600
[ Voice fades ]

441
00:36:23,915 --> 00:36:25,576
What are you doing?

442
00:36:29,387 --> 00:36:31,355
I'm rearranging my desk.

443
00:36:31,422 --> 00:36:34,084
You didn't like
the way it was before?

444
00:36:35,726 --> 00:36:37,284
I had no feelings about it.

445
00:36:37,361 --> 00:36:39,556
I'm merely attempting
to optimize.

446
00:36:42,600 --> 00:36:46,468
Sense offenders
holed up in the Nether.

447
00:37:00,718 --> 00:37:03,551
We estimate--
we estimate 50 men, sir.

448
00:37:03,621 --> 00:37:07,216
Intelligence tells us
they're all fully armed.

449
00:37:07,292 --> 00:37:10,921
This is the group that bombed
the Prozium factories.

450
00:37:10,995 --> 00:37:12,519
You clean, we'll sweep.

451
00:37:12,597 --> 00:37:14,121
Yes, sir.

452
00:37:14,199 --> 00:37:15,723
[ Indistinct shouting ]

453
00:37:17,135 --> 00:37:19,000
Go! Go! Go! Go!

454
00:37:19,070 --> 00:37:20,002
Go!

455
00:37:20,071 --> 00:37:21,663
Aah!

456
00:37:21,739 --> 00:37:24,139
Take it! Take the landings!

457
00:37:25,343 --> 00:37:26,332
- Aah!
- Aah!

458
00:37:37,822 --> 00:37:39,949
- Cover me. I'm going in.
- Aaaaaaaah!

459
00:37:43,828 --> 00:37:45,318
Nice grab, Cleric.

460
00:38:22,934 --> 00:38:25,368
[ Casings rattling ]

461
00:38:53,665 --> 00:38:55,326
[ Door rattles, creaks ]

462
00:38:57,402 --> 00:38:59,393
[ Door opens ]

463
00:39:00,738 --> 00:39:03,229
[ Stairs creaking ]

464
00:40:15,013 --> 00:40:18,915
"Ludwig Van Beethoven."

465
00:40:44,475 --> 00:40:46,466
[ Record scratching ]

466
00:41:13,538 --> 00:41:15,733
[ Powerful
classical music plays ]

467
00:41:42,233 --> 00:41:44,292
[ Music continues ]

468
00:42:17,602 --> 00:42:18,762
Cleric...

469
00:42:19,804 --> 00:42:21,294
Why didn't you leave that

470
00:42:21,372 --> 00:42:24,136
for the evidentiary team
to collect and log?

471
00:42:30,281 --> 00:42:31,714
They miss things sometimes.

472
00:42:31,783 --> 00:42:34,911
I'll take it in myself...

473
00:42:34,986 --> 00:42:37,784
make sure
it gets done properly.

474
00:42:39,624 --> 00:42:40,818
[ Sighs ]

475
00:42:40,892 --> 00:42:42,883
You know, Preston...

476
00:42:44,629 --> 00:42:46,790
If we keep burning
all this contraband,

477
00:42:46,864 --> 00:42:49,094
eventually there won't be
anything left to burn.

478
00:42:49,167 --> 00:42:52,967
What'll there be
for men like us?

479
00:42:53,037 --> 00:42:54,732
Sir!

480
00:42:54,806 --> 00:42:56,364
We got something out back.

481
00:42:56,441 --> 00:42:57,965
[ Men talking indistinctly ]

482
00:43:05,917 --> 00:43:08,283
We're gonna need
two more men on this.

483
00:43:12,323 --> 00:43:13,654
[ Barking ]

484
00:43:13,724 --> 00:43:16,056
These animals were defended
by women and children.

485
00:43:16,127 --> 00:43:17,424
We put them down easily.

486
00:43:17,495 --> 00:43:21,124
This isn't the first time
we've seen this.

487
00:43:21,199 --> 00:43:23,463
Why do they keep
these animals?

488
00:43:23,534 --> 00:43:25,661
What, do they--
do they eat them?

489
00:43:27,672 --> 00:43:29,799
What do you want me
to do, sir?

490
00:43:29,874 --> 00:43:31,171
Exterminate them, of course.

491
00:43:31,242 --> 00:43:32,675
All right. Let's do it.

492
00:43:32,743 --> 00:43:34,506
- No.
- [ Guns cocking ]

493
00:43:34,579 --> 00:43:35,773
What's wrong, Cleric?

494
00:43:39,350 --> 00:43:41,545
Nothing.

495
00:43:42,720 --> 00:43:44,483
[ Barking continues ]

496
00:43:47,258 --> 00:43:49,453
[ Gunshots, dogs whimpering ]

497
00:43:54,565 --> 00:43:56,055
- Hey...
- [ Dog running ]

498
00:43:56,133 --> 00:43:57,361
Grab it.

499
00:43:57,435 --> 00:43:58,527
Grab it!

500
00:44:06,277 --> 00:44:08,472
Sir... toss it back in.

501
00:44:08,546 --> 00:44:10,377
I'll finish it off.

502
00:44:14,285 --> 00:44:15,217
[ Gun cocks ]

503
00:44:15,286 --> 00:44:16,310
Give it to me, sir.

504
00:44:16,387 --> 00:44:18,321
Give it to him, Cleric.
He'll finish it.

505
00:44:24,829 --> 00:44:27,059
[ Whimpering ]

506
00:44:29,500 --> 00:44:32,230
[ Whimpering continues ]

507
00:44:32,303 --> 00:44:33,565
Wait!

508
00:44:36,574 --> 00:44:39,134
It seems to me that...

509
00:44:39,210 --> 00:44:42,873
at least some of these animals
ought to be tested for disease.

510
00:44:42,947 --> 00:44:44,972
If there's an epidemic
in the Nether,

511
00:44:45,049 --> 00:44:47,517
it's best we know about it.

512
00:44:50,521 --> 00:44:54,287
I don't quite follow
your logic, Cleric.

513
00:44:54,358 --> 00:44:55,620
They were Resistance.

514
00:44:55,692 --> 00:44:57,922
They could have led us
to the Underground.

515
00:44:57,995 --> 00:44:59,656
But instead of apprehension
and interrogation,

516
00:44:59,730 --> 00:45:00,697
they were slaughtered.

517
00:45:00,764 --> 00:45:03,927
Yes, but, Cleric,
given the circumstances,

518
00:45:04,001 --> 00:45:05,593
the Father has decreed

519
00:45:05,669 --> 00:45:09,070
that there will be no more
"process" for sense offenders.

520
00:45:09,139 --> 00:45:11,539
They are either to be
shot on sight

521
00:45:11,608 --> 00:45:13,098
or incinerated without a trial.

522
00:45:13,176 --> 00:45:14,302
But it's counter to law.

523
00:45:14,378 --> 00:45:16,209
You're a member
of the Council. If--

524
00:45:16,280 --> 00:45:18,145
It is not the will
of the Council,

525
00:45:18,215 --> 00:45:20,979
it is the will of Father--
and he is law.

526
00:45:22,619 --> 00:45:25,110
Sir...

527
00:45:25,188 --> 00:45:28,123
without the logic of process,
is it not just mayhem--

528
00:45:28,191 --> 00:45:31,183
what we have worked so hard
to eradicate?

529
00:45:31,261 --> 00:45:33,388
You must understand, Preston,

530
00:45:33,463 --> 00:45:37,058
that while you-- and even I--
may not always agree with it,

531
00:45:37,134 --> 00:45:39,830
it is not the message
that is important,

532
00:45:39,903 --> 00:45:43,134
it is our obedience to it.

533
00:45:43,206 --> 00:45:45,333
Father's will.

534
00:45:45,409 --> 00:45:48,003
Call it faith.

535
00:45:48,078 --> 00:45:50,103
You have it, I assume?

536
00:45:54,718 --> 00:45:56,049
Yes.

537
00:45:57,554 --> 00:45:59,112
I have it.

538
00:45:59,189 --> 00:46:00,747
Good.

539
00:46:06,430 --> 00:46:08,421
[ Click, whirring ]

540
00:46:09,967 --> 00:46:11,696
[ Click ]

541
00:46:11,768 --> 00:46:15,329
[ Click, whirring ]

542
00:46:22,112 --> 00:46:25,445
Confiscated evidence
